The paper deals with consensus algorithms in dynamic networks, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithms are designed to handle failures, which is a common concern in systems and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the time complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper involves information theory, as it deals with the convergence of agents' values to a common value (cs.IT).
